records.addlTxt:
Court finds State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing hearing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing.  Additional statements by R.D.B.

AS TO COUNT 2:
The court sentenced the defendant to 90 DAYS in the House of Correction (CONSECUTIVE), with credit for 76 DAYS time served.  

Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 12 MONTHS.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-Serve 5 DAYS in the House of Correction as Condition Time (as to COUNT 1), STAYED pending review;
-Batterers Intervention program;
-Mental health evaluation, comply with recommended treatment;
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment;
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent;
-Absolute sobriety;
-No contact with victim R.D.B. unless approved by the Court;
-Third party contact for the purpose of child visitation, third party to be approved by agent;
-Obtain/maintain employment;
-No contact with firearms;
-Provide DNA sample;
-Court WAIVES all non-mandatory court costs and fees;
-Pay all mandatory supervision fees, court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV surcharges during period of probation.  Unpaid amount to convert to a civil judgment;  

Defendant to report to probation intake and provide DNA sample by 4/29/2022.

*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.
*Court advised that under 18 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a crime of domestic violence.

Probation Review Hearing in Branch 35.
